The paper deals with visual content classification, specifically for tensor objects. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new network architecture for classification, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The experiments conducted involve video sequences, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of principal component analysis (PCA) suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
